\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {1}{\ignorespaces Master RF receiver chain used as the canonical scaffold for experiment-specific bench layouts, arranged as three centered section rows (Roof, Roof to Lab, Lab). Amplifiers are drawn with standard gain-triangle symbols; filters are shown as labeled RF blocks; connector transitions are annotated on the interconnects rather than drawn as separate blocks. Stage map (known manufacturer/part where available): A1/A2/A3 = Mini-Circuits ZKL-33ULN-S+ (rooftop, datasheet gain estimate $\sim +26$ dB each); F1 = Reactel 1420-15S11 (passband $\sim 1412$--$1428$ MHz, insertion-loss estimate $\sim 1$ dB); F2 = K\&L Microwave 5B120-1380/160-0 (passband $\sim 1300$--$1460$ MHz, insertion-loss estimate $\sim 2$ dB). A4/A5 are current bench amplifiers (nominally $\sim +20$ dB each), and C1 is the roof-lab coax with prior length estimate $\sim 35$ m.}}{2}{figure.1}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:block_diagram}{{1}{2}{Master RF receiver chain used as the canonical scaffold for experiment-specific bench layouts, arranged as three centered section rows (Roof, Roof to Lab, Lab). Amplifiers are drawn with standard gain-triangle symbols; filters are shown as labeled RF blocks; connector transitions are annotated on the interconnects rather than drawn as separate blocks. Stage map (known manufacturer/part where available): A1/A2/A3 = Mini-Circuits ZKL-33ULN-S+ (rooftop, datasheet gain estimate $\sim +26$ dB each); F1 = Reactel 1420-15S11 (passband $\sim 1412$--$1428$ MHz, insertion-loss estimate $\sim 1$ dB); F2 = K\&L Microwave 5B120-1380/160-0 (passband $\sim 1300$--$1460$ MHz, insertion-loss estimate $\sim 2$ dB). A4/A5 are current bench amplifiers (nominally $\sim +20$ dB each), and C1 is the roof-lab coax with prior length estimate $\sim 35$ m}{figure.1}{}}
